Lua vs Nim
==========

Lua:
	+ Dynamically typed
	+ Small language

	- Quirky language
	- Lacking in abstractions
	- Can't utilize big memory

Nim:
	+ Very high performance
	+ Threading and channels
	+ Very clean language
	+ Very high abstractions
	+ Much more evolved standard library
	+ Very good C/C++ integration
	+ A language with a very good potential for "evolving friction free"

	- Debugger not that well depeloped yet
	- Lesser IDE support, but there are plugins for several
	- A bit complex language, but every feature is well designed


Which one fits Urho best?

	- Lua is already integrated, to some extent.
	- Nim offers a smoother and much more performant integration, since it compiles to C/C++
	- Given Araq and c2nim I think we can quickly get a very good integration

	Answer: Nim

Which one fits our server side best?

	- Nim has very good performance
	- Nim's type system improves robustness
	- Nim has async code and support for ZeroMQ etc
	- Nim does threads and big memory

	Answer: Nim



	- Araq is looking for work, so we would have the super Nim hacker.
	- Araq actually started with Lua, then Python, now Nimrod.

